You have that aura.

550
00:28:13,047 --> 00:28:14,847
I brought some gifts for you all.
JARN KUB KAO

551
00:28:15,480 --> 00:28:17,160
Here, this is for you.

552
00:28:18,447 --> 00:28:19,480
This is for Kana.

553
00:28:20,520 --> 00:28:21,040
Thank you.

554
00:28:21,100 --> 00:28:22,706
And this is for you, ma'am.

555
00:28:23,340 --> 00:28:25,540
This brand is over 200 years old.

556
00:28:25,565 --> 00:28:27,880
It smells luxurious. Just perfect for you.

557
00:28:29,327 --> 00:28:30,440
Thank you so much.

558
00:28:30,593 --> 00:28:32,393
Wow, that's authentic.

559
00:28:32,533 --> 00:28:35,040
It's so expensive back home.

560
00:28:35,420 --> 00:28:36,620
That's not all.

561
00:28:38,127 --> 00:28:40,107
Here's a vintage wine from France.

562
00:28:40,287 --> 00:28:41,287
It's for you, sir.

563
00:28:42,073 --> 00:28:43,193
Oh, I love it.

564
00:28:44,333 --> 00:28:47,067
Would you like to have some wine with me?

565
00:28:50,267 --> 00:28:51,547
Are you serious?

566
00:28:52,927 --> 00:28:54,800
If you are, I'd love to keep you company.

567
00:28:55,773 --> 00:28:57,906
I'm talking about you and Kanit.

568
00:28:58,227 --> 00:28:59,300
Are you serious about him?

569
00:29:11,486 --> 00:29:13,419
I never date anyone casually.

570
00:29:16,513 --> 00:29:17,640
If you're serious about him,

571
00:29:19,686 --> 00:29:22,013
announce your wedding now. Do you dare?

572
00:29:28,120 --> 00:29:29,320
I'm not afraid to do it.

573
00:29:30,607 --> 00:29:33,280
If Kanit is okay, I can propose now.

574
00:29:33,727 --> 00:29:36,320
Hey, my dad is just kidding.

575
00:29:38,560 --> 00:29:39,560
But I'm not.

576
00:29:59,087 --> 00:30:00,607
I've loved you from the moment we met.

577
00:30:02,287 --> 00:30:04,400
I want to fly with you
for the rest of my life.

578
00:30:11,433 --> 00:30:12,433
Will you marry me?

579
00:30:24,920 --> 00:30:25,920
Pued!

580
00:30:26,113 --> 00:30:27,683
Pued has a fishbone stuck in his throat!

581
00:30:27,707 --> 00:30:28,707
Please don't!

582
00:30:35,480 --> 00:30:36,969
Don't shove your finger down your throat.

583
00:30:36,993 --> 00:30:38,513
It'll push the fish bone further down.

584
00:30:39,040 --> 00:30:40,520
Here, have some water. Take it slow.

585
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:42,040
Slowly.

586
00:30:42,466 --> 00:30:43,673
Small sips.

587
00:30:46,093 --> 00:30:47,213
A little more.

588
00:30:50,440 --> 00:30:51,440
Are you feeling better?

589
00:30:51,618 --> 00:30:52,618
Yes.

590
00:30:52,647 --> 00:30:53,920
Thank you so much.

591
00:30:54,253 --> 00:30:56,040
I thought I wouldn't make it.

592
00:30:59,153 --> 00:31:02,040
A captain can do that?

593
00:31:02,193 --> 00:31:03,953
I thought we'd have to
call in a rescue team.

594
00:31:08,927 --> 00:31:11,327
We had emergency first-aid training.

595
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:19,000
In fact, captains undergo training and
practical exams on safety procedures too.

596
00:31:19,126 --> 00:31:21,380
Even though our main duty
is to command the aircraft,

597
00:31:21,433 --> 00:31:25,580
the safety of our passengers
is our highest responsibility

598
00:31:25,607 --> 00:31:27,040
and our top priority.

599
00:31:31,273 --> 00:31:33,420
This is my son-in-law.

600
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:36,040
He's amazing.

601
00:31:41,080 --> 00:31:42,160
You're amazing.

602
00:31:42,353 --> 00:31:45,080
Everyone in my family
was so impressed by you.

603
00:31:45,260 --> 00:31:46,280
Did you hear it?

604
00:31:46,612 --> 00:31:49,960
Your dad officially announced me
as his son-in-law.

605
00:31:50,313 --> 00:31:51,586
Hold on.

606
00:31:51,700 --> 00:31:53,640
Don't celebrate just yet.

607
00:31:53,800 --> 00:31:57,473
My dad accepted you as a son-in-law
because you're a captain.

608
00:31:57,653 --> 00:32:01,640
Come on. By the time he finds
out the truth, he'll already love me.

609
00:32:03,227 --> 00:32:04,840
Alright, he might scold me a little,

610
00:32:05,020 --> 00:32:08,080
but eventually,
he'll take me in as his son-in-law.

611
00:32:08,913 --> 00:32:10,320
And what was that earlier?

612
00:32:10,760 --> 00:32:12,440
We just started dating,

613
00:32:12,540 --> 00:32:14,940
but you suddenly proposed like that.

614
00:32:15,386 --> 00:32:17,133
Wasn't that too much acting?

615
00:32:17,158 --> 00:32:18,158
Come on.

616
00:32:18,760 --> 00:32:20,760
It's not Toto without being extra.

617
00:32:24,633 --> 00:32:26,073
I saw you, though.

618
00:32:26,532 --> 00:32:28,040
When I was proposing,

619
00:32:28,993 --> 00:32:31,680
your eyes were about to say yes.

620
00:32:33,427 --> 00:32:36,240
I was just playing along.

621
00:32:36,265 --> 00:32:37,705
- Just going with the flow.
- Really?

622
00:32:37,813 --> 00:32:38,813
- Yeah.
- Hmm?

623
00:32:38,973 --> 00:32:39,688
- Hey.
- What?

624
00:32:39,713 --> 00:32:40,373
Just think about it.

625
00:32:40,398 --> 00:32:42,806
If I said no, we'd have been caught.

626
00:32:42,860 --> 00:32:43,860
Would you dare say no?

627
00:32:44,293 --> 00:32:44,846
Hmm?

628
00:32:44,871 --> 00:32:45,871
Hey, stop.

629
00:32:46,013 --> 00:32:48,840
Let's make sure we get away with it
this time first.

630
00:32:49,147 --> 00:32:51,280
I'll find time to tell my dad myself.

631
00:32:52,493 --> 00:32:54,846
But thank you for today.

632
00:32:55,233 --> 00:32:58,945
Thank you for being my handsome, cool,
and sharp boyfriend.

633
00:32:59,433 --> 00:33:01,360
Don't you have a reward
for this handsome guy?

634
00:33:03,467 --> 00:33:04,467
What reward?

635
00:33:04,733 --> 00:33:05,733
Come on.

636
00:33:16,720 --> 00:33:17,720
Hmm?

637
00:33:18,133 --> 00:33:19,133
- What?
- That's it?

638
00:33:20,280 --> 00:33:21,040
Come on.

639
00:33:21,153 --> 00:33:22,240
I barely got to enjoy it.

640
00:33:22,793 --> 00:33:25,760
I even left the rescue vehicle
to fly an airplane.

641
00:33:26,300 --> 00:33:27,300
That's all I get?

642
00:33:29,319 --> 00:33:30,319
Bummer.

643
00:33:38,453 --> 00:33:39,453
Enough?

644
00:33:39,806 --> 00:33:41,000
If that's not enough,

645
00:33:41,853 --> 00:33:43,200
I'll give you more tonight.

646
00:33:43,973 --> 00:33:45,160
It's not enough.

647
00:33:47,533 --> 00:33:48,733
Get in the car.

648
00:33:49,913 --> 00:33:50,913
Come on.

649
00:33:51,186 --> 00:33:52,186
Hey.

650
00:33:52,211 --> 00:33:53,211
Hurry up.

651
00:34:03,100 --> 00:34:05,040
You haven't picked up my calls
since yesterday.

652
00:34:09,360 --> 00:34:11,120
Are you training for the Spartan Race?

653
00:34:14,287 --> 00:34:15,680
Do you really like me?

654
00:34:17,213 --> 00:34:18,320
I already told you.

655
00:34:18,345 --> 00:34:19,760
I was a pimple-faced kid.

656
00:34:20,067 --> 00:34:21,400
You even threw away my gift.

657
00:34:22,400 --> 00:34:23,880
Why do you like me now?

658
00:34:25,760 --> 00:34:27,360
It's because I got more handsome, right?

659
00:34:29,133 --> 00:34:30,280
Who said I threw it away?

660
00:34:34,207 --> 00:34:35,487
I still have it.

661
00:34:59,440 --> 00:35:02,080
Yeah, it's true that I like you
because you're handsome.

662
00:35:02,333 --> 00:35:03,440
I'm not bullshitting you.

663
00:35:04,780 --> 00:35:06,420
But I like who you are on the inside too.

664
00:35:07,367 --> 00:35:09,227
That doesn't make me feel any better.

665
00:35:13,913 --> 00:35:15,200
Alright, are you ready?

666
00:35:15,780 --> 00:35:16,780
It's time.

667
00:35:18,033 --> 00:35:20,320
I have a session with my trainer.
You should go.

668
00:35:20,800 --> 00:35:21,960
I have nothing left to say.

669
00:35:23,820 --> 00:35:25,580
I'm going to join the
Spartan Race with you.

670
00:35:26,413 --> 00:35:28,000
I'm not giving up that easily.

671
00:35:28,367 --> 00:35:30,120
I'm going to seriously pursue you

672
00:35:31,500 --> 00:35:33,360
until you accept me.

673
00:35:42,040 --> 00:35:43,040
Let's go.

674
00:35:51,133 --> 00:35:52,780
You wear this uniform every day?

675
00:35:52,880 --> 00:35:54,480
I have to get ready to fly later.

676
00:35:54,600 --> 00:35:56,240
I stopped by to see you two off.

677
00:35:58,107 --> 00:35:59,360
Sorry for the trouble.

678
00:35:59,580 --> 00:36:00,527
Are you going to be late?

679
00:36:00,552 --> 00:36:01,600
It's no trouble at all.

680
00:36:02,133 --> 00:36:03,326
Taking care of Kanit's family

681
00:36:03,480 --> 00:36:04,480
is my pleasure.

682
00:36:04,560 --> 00:36:05,560
I should go.

683
00:36:05,927 --> 00:36:06,927
Alright.

684
00:36:07,033 --> 00:36:08,349
Take good care of Dad and Mom, Kana.

685
00:36:08,373 --> 00:36:09,373
I know.

686
00:36:11,660 --> 00:36:12,920
Take good care of each other.

687
00:36:13,519 --> 00:36:14,519
We will.

688
00:36:14,544 --> 00:36:14,953
Let's go.

689
00:36:14,978 --> 00:36:16,000
Let me walk you over.

690
00:36:19,707 --> 00:36:20,707
Take care.

691
00:36:20,732 --> 00:36:21,732
Thank you.

692
00:36:34,532 --> 00:36:35,532
Whoa.

693
00:36:35,847 --> 00:36:37,000
I didn't think I'd make it.

694
00:36:37,033 --> 00:36:38,360
I felt so pressured.

695
00:36:38,440 --> 00:36:41,640
Oh, you're amazing.

696
00:36:41,786 --> 00:36:43,186
I almost believed you.

697
00:36:43,240 --> 00:36:46,240
Of course. I look like a captain.

698
00:36:47,727 --> 00:36:48,727
Wait, no.

699
00:36:49,126 --> 00:36:51,440
I think I'm more handsome than
that thick-browed captain.

700
00:36:51,673 --> 00:36:53,826
Hey, why are you talking about him?

701
00:36:53,851 --> 00:36:54,851
Stop that.

702
00:36:55,180 --> 00:36:56,960
You're definitely the most handsome.

703
00:37:00,940 --> 00:37:02,360
Alright, I'm off to fly.

704
00:37:02,906 --> 00:37:03,693
Under the highway.

705
00:37:03,725 --> 00:37:04,725
Wait.

706
00:37:08,480 --> 00:37:09,480
Thank you.

707
00:37:18,907 --> 00:37:19,907
Go.

708
00:37:37,627 --> 00:37:38,873
Hey!

709
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:40,360
Keep it down! I'm trying to sleep!

710
00:37:40,420 --> 00:37:42,780
No. I have to prove my love.

711
00:37:43,227 --> 00:37:44,787
You're even in disguise to prove yours.

712
00:37:45,173 --> 00:37:46,560
I have to do it my way.

713
00:37:50,007 --> 00:37:51,320
Damn. Look at our lives.

714
00:37:51,647 --> 00:37:52,760
We have to work,

715
00:37:53,033 --> 00:37:54,393
and we have to make our love work.

716
00:37:54,986 --> 00:37:56,600
Why is it so freaking hard?

717
00:37:57,507 --> 00:37:58,789
Well, we fell for them on our own.

718
00:37:58,813 --> 00:37:59,933
They didn't even ask for it.

719
00:38:00,080 --> 00:38:01,560
You're right.

720
00:38:02,020 --> 00:38:03,080
(Requesting rescue unit.)

721
00:38:03,473 --> 00:38:06,040
(62-year-old male, heart attack.)

722
00:38:06,367 --> 00:38:08,000
(Experiencing chest pain in a taxi.)

723
00:38:08,147 --> 00:38:10,840
(Location: Bangna-Trat Road.
(History of heart disease.)

724
00:38:11,007 --> 00:38:12,327
(Rescue unit needed immediately.)

725
00:38:13,633 --> 00:38:14,367
You don't have to go.

726
00:38:14,392 --> 00:38:15,120
I will.

727
00:38:15,145 --> 00:38:16,705
I'll ask Beer and Ja-O to come with me.

728
00:38:17,913 --> 00:38:18,600
Mm.

729
00:38:18,700 --> 00:38:20,040
But aren't those two off today?

730
00:38:21,506 --> 00:38:23,826
You and I are going. Hurry.
I think we can make it in time.

731
00:38:29,126 --> 00:38:30,494
THE WINNERS RESCUE FOUNDATION

732
00:38:40,167 --> 00:38:41,167
Help!

733
00:38:43,200 --> 00:38:44,200
Ma'am.

734
00:38:45,900 --> 00:38:48,367
Why are you wearing a rescue uniform?

735
00:38:49,740 --> 00:38:50,740
How is he?

736
00:38:52,212 --> 00:38:54,760
He suddenly became weak
and couldn't speak.

737
00:38:54,853 --> 00:38:56,293
Let's get him out.

738
00:38:57,700 --> 00:38:58,700
Ready?

739
00:39:10,480 --> 00:39:12,880
How long ago was your father doing fine
before this happened?

740
00:39:13,099 --> 00:39:14,480
Around half an hour.

741
00:39:15,467 --> 00:39:17,480
Ki, get ready to monitor his vital signs.

742
00:39:17,613 --> 00:39:18,613
Okay.

743
00:39:22,420 --> 00:39:23,420
Sir.

744
00:39:23,487 --> 00:39:24,487
Sir.

745
00:39:24,800 --> 00:39:25,920
Sir, can you hear me?

746
00:39:34,673 --> 00:39:35,673
Don't worry.

747
00:39:36,280 --> 00:39:37,560
We're waiting for the ambulance.

748
00:40:07,639 --> 00:40:09,480
Hey. How's my dad?

749
00:40:10,773 --> 00:40:12,040
He's with the doctors now.

750
00:40:13,293 --> 00:40:14,413
He'll be okay.

751
00:40:30,673 --> 00:40:31,953
Why did you lie?

752
00:40:32,993 --> 00:40:35,040
Do you have any idea how he would feel?

753
00:40:51,833 --> 00:40:52,833
Coffee?

754
00:40:55,833 --> 00:40:56,833
Thank you.

755
00:41:03,593 --> 00:41:04,620
I'm sorry.

756
00:41:06,146 --> 00:41:07,146
I…

757
00:41:07,553 --> 00:41:08,993
I ruined our plan.

758
00:41:11,380 --> 00:41:12,680
It really was a coincidence.

759
00:41:14,087 --> 00:41:15,400
Why are you apologizing?

760
00:41:16,060 --> 00:41:17,427
You saved my dad's life.

761
00:41:17,940 --> 00:41:19,920
My family owes you.

762
00:41:21,193 --> 00:41:22,193
I guess

763
00:41:22,253 --> 00:41:24,040
I'll have to work off our debt.

764
00:41:24,320 --> 00:41:27,080
You don't have to. I was just doing my job.

765
00:41:29,307 --> 00:41:31,747
I'm just worried your dad's
going to lose it when he wakes up.

766
00:41:32,013 --> 00:41:33,280
What if he relapses?

767
00:41:33,640 --> 00:41:35,920
This isn't how I wanted
him to find out, either.

768
00:41:39,120 --> 00:41:40,600
But I'm kinda relieved.

769
00:41:43,193 --> 00:41:48,120
It's exhausting pretending to like
someone who's not the real you.

770
00:41:50,239 --> 00:41:54,000
Honestly, I like Toto, the rescuer,

771
00:41:55,240 --> 00:41:56,600
not Toto, the captain.

772
00:42:08,913 --> 00:42:09,960
Your dad will be okay,

773
00:42:11,853 --> 00:42:14,953
and he'll accept me as Toto, the rescuer.

774
00:42:15,700 --> 00:42:17,620
The new boyfriend of Kanit,
the flight attendant.

775
00:42:19,873 --> 00:42:21,280
We'll get through this together.

776
00:42:34,967 --> 00:42:36,400
No more captain's uniform?

777
00:42:37,399 --> 00:42:38,879
Did you come straight from gardening?

778
00:42:39,167 --> 00:42:40,567
That's a fertilizer giveaway shirt.

779
00:42:43,566 --> 00:42:44,566
Hello, sir.

780
00:42:44,947 --> 00:42:45,987
Hello, ma'am.

781
00:42:48,419 --> 00:42:50,139
He greeted you.
Why didn't you say anything?

782
00:42:50,280 --> 00:42:52,680
He saved your life.

783
00:42:52,947 --> 00:42:54,627
Not even a thank you?

784
00:42:55,693 --> 00:42:57,960
It's alright. I was just doing my job.

785
00:42:59,347 --> 00:43:02,480
Dad, you don't like that
he's just a rescuer, do you?

786
00:43:02,627 --> 00:43:03,627
No.

787
00:43:04,700 --> 00:43:05,907
I don't like that he lied.

788
00:43:10,199 --> 00:43:11,199
I'm sorry.

789
00:43:13,560 --> 00:43:16,840
I'm sorry, sir.
I'm sorry, ma'am, for lying.

790
00:43:20,547 --> 00:43:22,496
I lied to everyone in your family.
I'm really sorry.

791
00:43:22,520 --> 00:43:23,880
You said you were serious.

792
00:43:25,993 --> 00:43:27,233
Are you sure you weren't lying?

793
00:43:27,507 --> 00:43:28,507
Dad,

794
00:43:28,746 --> 00:43:30,600
all of this was actually my idea.

795
00:43:31,633 --> 00:43:34,769
I told him to dress as a captain
to fool everyone.

796
00:43:35,160 --> 00:43:36,360
You knew it was wrong.

797
00:43:38,140 --> 00:43:41,276
Instead of stopping each other,
you encouraged it?

798
00:43:42,213 --> 00:43:43,400
How is that even okay?

799
00:43:43,926 --> 00:43:45,526
Why did you do this?

800
00:43:46,707 --> 00:43:48,600
Do you think I really enjoy this?

801
00:43:49,080 --> 00:43:52,680
Do you know how much Dad's expectations
have weighed me down my whole life?

802
00:43:53,987 --> 00:43:54,926
Always having to land a good job,

803
00:43:54,951 --> 00:43:55,753
get good grades,

804
00:43:55,827 --> 00:43:57,440
and even find a good partner

805
00:43:58,006 --> 00:43:59,560
who's rich and good at making money.

806
00:43:59,678 --> 00:44:02,278
Why? Can't it just be someone ordinary?

807
00:44:02,779 --> 00:44:04,047
Is just loving each other not enough?

808
00:44:04,071 --> 00:44:05,600
Can't he just be a rescuer?

809
00:44:07,767 --> 00:44:11,640
You need money to live, no matter what.

810
00:44:14,193 --> 00:44:15,880
Love alone doesn't pay the bills.

811
00:44:16,800 --> 00:44:18,040
Stop being so naive.

812
00:44:24,720 --> 00:44:26,400
If you're going to keep seeing each other,

813
00:44:26,887 --> 00:44:28,520
you better improve your life.

814
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,840
Make yourself worthy of my son.

815
00:44:34,620 --> 00:44:37,240
If you can't do that, then break up.

816
00:44:52,267 --> 00:44:53,307
Are you okay?

817
00:44:54,473 --> 00:44:55,520
You've been quiet.

818
00:44:58,080 --> 00:45:00,840
I'm sorry about what my dad said

819
00:45:01,793 --> 00:45:04,120
and for asking you to pretend.

820
00:45:05,599 --> 00:45:07,200
A few harsh words won't shake me.

821
00:45:07,619 --> 00:45:08,819
It was nothing.

822
00:45:10,827 --> 00:45:11,867
Are you okay?

823
00:45:13,800 --> 00:45:15,320
I'm used to it.

824
00:45:16,273 --> 00:45:18,306
My dad is rarely proud of anything I do.

825
00:45:18,540 --> 00:45:21,040
So I guess I don't stand a chance, huh?

826
00:45:23,333 --> 00:45:25,240
I see things differently from your dad.

827
00:45:26,780 --> 00:45:27,786
To me, it doesn't matter

828
00:45:27,985 --> 00:45:29,345
if I have enough to get by or not.

829
00:45:29,433 --> 00:45:31,146
It doesn't matter if I'm dirt poor.

830
00:45:31,260 --> 00:45:32,440
I can sleep anywhere.

831
00:45:32,553 --> 00:45:35,600
Just don't make me sleep near a cheater.

832
00:45:44,940 --> 00:45:46,240
I don't care anymore.

833
00:45:47,287 --> 00:45:49,400
If he wants to disown me, let him.

834
00:45:50,527 --> 00:45:51,480
I want you as my boyfriend.

835
00:45:51,505 --> 00:45:53,105
Hey, don't say that.

836
00:45:55,940 --> 00:45:57,753
I understand your dad's concerns.

837
00:46:00,207 --> 00:46:04,240
He wants you to meet
someone who can really take care of you.

838
00:46:04,306 --> 00:46:06,560
Hey, I can take care of myself.

839
00:46:07,647 --> 00:46:10,520
I just want love.

840
00:46:15,479 --> 00:46:17,346
But love alone isn't enough.

841
00:46:18,780 --> 00:46:20,220
Life has expenses.

842
00:46:21,400 --> 00:46:23,467
I eat cheap. You eat expensive.

843
00:46:24,313 --> 00:46:26,076
What if one day I can't afford
to eat with you?

844
00:46:26,100 --> 00:46:27,780
Then I'll pay for you.

845
00:46:28,259 --> 00:46:29,466
I can eat cheap with you.

846
00:46:29,491 --> 00:46:31,040
But I can't eat expensive with you.

847
00:46:40,240 --> 00:46:41,240
Don't worry.

848
00:46:41,620 --> 00:46:42,640
I'm not giving up.

849
00:46:43,026 --> 00:46:46,840
I'll prove to your dad
that I'm the best for you.

850
00:46:49,247 --> 00:46:50,247
Thank you.

851
00:46:50,640 --> 00:46:53,279
You never give up. That's why I like you.

852
00:46:55,080 --> 00:46:56,240
Isn't it because I'm spicy?

853
00:46:56,265 --> 00:46:59,606
Well, a little.
♪ All the storms that have come to pass ♪

854
00:46:59,860 --> 00:47:02,906
♪ Keep them as mere memories ♪

855
00:47:02,980 --> 00:47:06,786
♪ But here today it's you and I ♪

856
00:47:06,967 --> 00:47:11,080
♪ We've proved this
love could carry us high ♪

857
00:47:11,320 --> 00:47:15,040
♪ No matter how hard the journey was ♪

858
00:47:15,180 --> 00:47:19,107
♪ In the end we arrived,
completed a good flight ♪

859
00:47:25,446 --> 00:47:27,601
(Next Episode)
Why have you been seeing me a lot lately?

860
00:47:27,625 --> 00:47:29,006
Because he's busy.

861
00:47:29,031 --> 00:47:30,943
He's working multiple
shifts and jobs right now.

862
00:47:30,967 --> 00:47:33,800
You need to bring back
the spark in your relationship.

863
00:47:33,920 --> 00:47:35,194
Sir, if you'd like to have some,

864
00:47:35,218 --> 00:47:37,020
please use your mouth.

865
00:47:37,240 --> 00:47:38,240
I'll start eating now.

866
00:47:38,500 --> 00:47:41,360
Since we started dating,
we've had no time for each other.

867
00:47:41,540 --> 00:47:44,080
I've been trying to find days
off from flying to see you,

868
00:47:44,787 --> 00:47:46,520
but you always have somewhere else to go.

869
00:47:46,707 --> 00:47:48,027
Are you working a lot these days?

870
00:47:48,207 --> 00:47:49,367
Why do you look so exhausted?

871
00:47:49,727 --> 00:47:51,400
Is this rescuer not good enough?

872
00:47:51,640 --> 00:47:52,920
I don't get to sleep.

873
00:47:53,340 --> 00:47:54,522
I don't even get to spend time with him.

874
00:47:54,546 --> 00:47:56,016
Is what I've been doing really worth it?

875
00:47:56,040 --> 00:47:57,960
If you're exhausted, why
don't you take a break?

